FBIS3-34453 "drnes027dd_94002" FBIS-NES-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 Palestinian Affairs Al-'Asifah Forces Claim Attack on Chemical Factory JN0802194694 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in Arabic 1730 GMT 8 Feb 94 JN0802194694 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] A military spokesman for the General Command of the al-'Asifah Forces -- the command of the Fatah forces inside the occupied territories -- has stated the following: Our cells operating inside the occupied homeland have planted advanced explosive charges in the Haifa chemical factory north of the industrial zone, which is adjacent to the Haifa oil refineries. The charges went off at 1300 on 7 February destroying the factory and setting huge fires that spread to neighboring factories and installations. The military spokesman added that, since the operation, rescue and fire fighting teams, the police, and the mobile environment protection unit for treating dangerous materials have been making great attempts to place the situation under control, while clouds of black smoke covered the whole Gulf of Haifa.
